  "dimension_notes": {
    "design_coherence": {
      "evidence": [
        "`useSharedLightboxState` defines a very wide cross-concern contract (`UseSharedLightboxStateProps` and `UseSharedLightboxStateReturn`) and still orchestrates variants, navigation, shot actions, lineage, references, layout, and button wiring in one hook (`src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/hooks/useSharedLightboxState.ts:53-138`, `:144-218`, `:631-735`).",
        "`useTimelineOrchestrator` exposes a very large API surface and combines timeline geometry, drag/drop, zoom, pending-state bookkeeping, selection, structure-video placement, and browser-modal UI state in a single hook (`src/tools/travel-between-images/components/Timeline/hooks/useTimelineOrchestrator.ts:21-139`, `:141-520`).",
        "Travel generation settings are repeatedly re-shaped across controller and service boundaries (`useGenerationController` maps join/motion/prompt bags to a request DTO, then request builder maps again to transport payload), increasing translation layers and drift risk (`src/tools/travel-between-images/components/ShotEditor/controllers/useGenerationController.ts:45-153`, `src/tools/travel-between-images/components/ShotEditor/services/generateVideo/types.ts:80-114`, `src/tools/travel-between-images/components/ShotEditor/services/generateVideo/requestBody.ts:21-73`).",
        "Large UI containers continue to combine presentation with data orchestration and side-effect policy (task prefetch/query resolution/shot mutations/lightbox wiring) instead of using thinner view models (`src/shared/components/MediaGalleryItem.tsx:128-203`, `src/shared/components/ShotImageManager/ShotImageManagerDesktop.tsx:120-177`, `src/shared/components/TasksPane/TasksPane.tsx:90-220`)."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "confidence": "high",
      "issues_preventing_higher_score": ""
    },
    "error_consistency": {
      "evidence": [
        "src/shared/components/MediaGallery/hooks/useMediaGalleryActions.ts:217-251 throws inside XMLHttpRequest callbacks; those throws are outside the enclosing try/catch at :212-258, so failures bypass local handleError and can surface as uncaught async errors.",
        "src/shared/components/MediaGallery/hooks/useMediaGalleryActions.ts:257 clears download state in finally immediately after xhr.send(), before request completion, creating misleading success/failure timing.",
        "src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/hooks/inpainting/useEditModePersistence.ts:37-39 and :76 silently swallow persistence/read failures with bare catch returning null/void, while neighboring modules typically call handleError/reportRuntimeError.",
        "src/shared/components/ChunkLoadErrorBoundary.tsx:48-53 catches and reloads without logging context, while src/app/components/error/AppErrorBoundary.tsx:40-49 records structured error context via handleError.",
        "src/pages/Home/components/panes/PhilosophyPane.tsx:124-126 and :165-167 and src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/components/VideoEditModeDisplay.tsx:161 swallow play() failures without logging or user feedback."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
